    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="986"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d986">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">British Embassy</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">memorandum</hi>
                </p>
                <p>In reply to British Embassy’s memorandum of the 11th instant with reference to
                    the supposed plan of a number of German liners in American ports to prepare to
                    sail at short notice and participate in belligerent operations in conjunction
                    with German cruisers now in Pacific waters, the Department of State has to state
                    that the United States Government is continuing its customary vigilance to
                    maintain the neutrality of the United States.</p>
                <p>With reference to the responsibility of the United States in this respect as a
                    neutral in the present war, the Department of State has the honor to refer the
                    British Embassy to the note of the Secretary of State to Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_BSC1">Colville Barclay</persName>, Chargé d’Affaires of Great
                    Britain, dated the 19th of August last.<note n="1" xml:id="d986fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_599">p. 599</ref>
                    </note>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,</closer>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-16">
                        <hi rend="italic">November 16, 1914</hi>.</date>
                </dateline>
            </div>
